Group Internal Audit Manager
A Leading HR Consulting Company in UAE
Dubai, UAE
Posted on: 29 Apr 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
This position is with one of our client based in United Arab Emirates and they are looking for a Group Internal Audit Manager who will be responsible to establish and manage an Internal Audit function to independently reviewing organizational activity, processes, operations, functions to determine whether these are efficiently and effectively being carried out as per the approved set of policies and procedures and also assess that these activities are functioning in accordance with management instructions and company governance measures. Identify risk areas and recommend opportunities to improve operating performance, and suggest solutions to problems where and when appropriate.
Make sure that the Internal Auditing process is designed to add value and improve the Group's operations. And helps an organization accomplish its objectives by bringing a systematic, disciplined approach to evaluate and improve the effectiveness of risk management, control, and governance processes.
REQUIREMENTS
